see \*(L"wait\*(R" in perlfunc.
.IP "waitpid" 8
.IX Item "waitpid"
Wait for a child process to change state.  This is identical to Perl's
builtin \f(CW\*(C`waitpid()\*(C'\fR function, see \*(L"waitpid\*(R" in perlfunc.
.Sp
.Vb 2
\&        $pid = POSIX::waitpid( \-1, POSIX::WNOHANG );
\&        print "status = ", ($? / 256), "\en";
.Ve
.IP "wcstombs" 8
